The order of the script is as follows: Opening - First word - Second word - Third word - Fourth word - Fifth word - Sixth word - Seventh word - Eighth word - Ninth word - Results - Closing remarks.

In the opening, explain the participation method, materials needed, and topic for today's game. 

Choose words that fit the topic and provide explanations for each word. 

To give time for writing, insert about 20 seconds of waiting music. 

In the results, encourage participation by discussing thoughts on today's game and explain the advantages of the game. 

After the results, insert about 30 seconds of waiting music for discussion time.

When closing, include a remark expressing that playing the game together today was really fun and suggest meeting again next time for more.
